messages.content: Hey! Planning Barcelona trip. What's everyone's budget?
Budget? 😅 Hostels under $30/night. Park bench works too
Mike 😂 I need 4-star with spa and pool. No shared bathrooms
Stayed at Hotel Arts last year. Amazing views and breakfast
€300/night? I could buy a car 😂 Paying for my room?
Need walking distance to beach. Casa Bonay has rooftop terrace 📸
Priorities! 😄 Near restaurants and nightlife. Gothic Quarter?
You haven't tried Barceloneta! Need hotel near good tapas
Same hotel or split? Spreadsheet with €50-€300 options. Loyalty points?
Ryan 😂 Spreadsheet in group chat? I have expired Groupon vouchers
Hilton Diamond here. Prefer unique over chain hotels
Can we agree on WiFi quality? Need to post pics in real-time
Hotel Omm - Michelin restaurant, rooftop pool, €200/night. Thoughts?
Still too expensive. Generator Hostel €60. For people who remember money
Stayed at Generator. Need private room with blackout curtains
Airbnb in El Born? €120/night, sleeps 4. We could split
Too many Airbnb disasters. Hotels have real people to complain to
Boutique hotel last year had tiny rooms. Had to step outside
Hotels with good cancellation? Also, gym facilities?
Work out on vacation? That's like ordering salad at a buffet 😂
Pet-friendly? Just kidding. Need late check-in, flight at 11pm
Most hotels have 24/7 reception. Need good soundproofing
Compromise? €80-€150 range? Prioritize location and amenities
Reasonable. I'm booking luxury suite. You enjoy budget, I'll enjoy jacuzzi 😉
Can I visit your jacuzzi? I'll bring my own towel
This is ridiculous 😂 Hotel Casa Fuster? Historic, on Passeig de Gràcia
Great suggestion! Close to restaurants. Check reviews?
Deep dive on reviews tonight. Checking for hidden fees
You're doing the Lord's work! Hidden fees are the worst
Ryan, let us know findings. Check availability. Book now or wait?
Eternal dilemma. Book with free cancellation and watch prices
Smart move! Need good AC. Last time in Rome it was a fan and ice
Horror story! AC is non-negotiable. No rustic charm sweat puddles
Overthinking this. Pick a place and deal with issues there
Spoken like someone who never shared bathroom with 12 strangers! Let's decide
